                            routine vet visits, toys, and
                            emergencies.</p>
                        <p class="c-light f-18 l-h-26 f-w-5 montserrat">But the real surprise? Unexpected vet bills.
                            One surgery or chronic illness can
                            wipe out a savings account. That’s where pet insurance offers value—by reducing the
                            financial blow of unexpected care.</p>
                        <p class="c-light f-18 l-h-26 f-w-5 montserrat">Think of insurance as a buffer against those
                            surprise costs. It won't cover
                            everything, but it can turn <span class="c-orange">a $3,000</span> bill into a
                            manageable <span class="c-orange">$600</span> expense, depending on
                            your plan. When budgeting for pet ownership, factor in insurance as a monthly cost that
                            protects you—and your pet—from the unpredictable.</p>
